1
00:05:08,174 --> 00:05:10,665
<i>One female in her late thirties
and three minors.</i>

2
00:05:10,777 --> 00:05:13,473
<i>Multiple stab wounds
and blunt-force trauma.</i>

3
00:05:13,579 --> 00:05:17,310
<i>What about the ex-husband? Court said
the wife had a restraining order against him.</i>

4
00:05:17,417 --> 00:05:20,750
Dylan Bennet. He spent the night
with a bottle of Jack Daniel's.

5
00:05:20,853 --> 00:05:23,686
<i>- It was his first Christmas without
his family. - All the more reason.</i>

6
00:05:23,790 --> 00:05:25,655
<i>Well, you didn't see him
when he ID-ed his family.</i>

7
00:05:25,758 --> 00:05:27,419
<i>Looked like he'd
been hit by a freight train.</i>

8
00:05:27,527 --> 00:05:31,657
<i>Seeing his kids like that. All the blood.
Yeah, it was definitely a nightmare for him.</i>

9
00:05:31,764 --> 00:05:35,427
<i>If this guy did it, he gets my vote
for a goddamn Academy Award.</i>

10
00:05:35,535 --> 00:05:38,197
Let's say the stepfather,
this Grady Edwards did it.

11
00:05:38,304 --> 00:05:40,101
- What do we got on him?
- Nothing.

12
00:05:40,206 --> 00:05:41,400
Said he was from Kansas.

13
00:05:41,507 --> 00:05:43,475
<i>Except we can't find a match
in any database.</i>

14
00:05:43,576 --> 00:05:45,874
<i>And he stopped the newspaper
to have time to disappear.</i>

15
00:05:45,978 --> 00:05:48,139
And we think
he might have done this before.

16
00:05:48,247 --> 00:05:51,216
<i>Three years ago in New Jersey,
a wife and three kids.</i>

17
00:05:51,317 --> 00:05:54,878
<i>Gunshot wounds to the back of the head.
The stepfather disappeared.</i>

18
00:05:55,321 --> 00:05:57,289
<i>Lived in a rented room
where he met the victims.</i>

19
00:05:57,390 --> 00:05:59,551
<i>Both rooms were owned by older women.</i>

20
00:05:59,659 --> 00:06:01,559
<i>One of the women
who lives in New Jersey said,</i>

21
00:06:01,661 --> 00:06:05,028
<i>"He's a wonderful man,
always paid his rent on time and in cash. "</i>

22
00:06:05,131 --> 00:06:07,429
<i>So, of course,
she never asked him for any identification.</i>

23
00:06:07,533 --> 00:06:10,559
<i>No, he's smart. The Toyota Land Cruiser
that we found abandoned?</i>

24
00:06:10,670 --> 00:06:13,969
<i>Paid for in cash. No driver's
license required for registration.</i>

25
00:06:14,073 --> 00:06:16,735
<i>No credit cards, no anything. Which means...</i>

26
00:06:16,843 --> 00:06:20,609
<i>- No photo ID required.
- Always a divorced or widowed situation.</i>

27
00:06:20,713 --> 00:06:23,375
I'm telling you, this guy's a monster.

28
00:06:27,387 --> 00:06:28,979
Even if this is your guy,

29
00:06:29,088 --> 00:06:32,114
<i>it's been six months.
He could be anywhere by now.</i>

30
00:06:42,201 --> 00:06:44,192
Mom, Beth says I can't get these.

31
00:06:44,303 --> 00:06:45,998
- Sean, we're not getting these.
- Hey! You two stop arguing.

32
00:06:46,105 --> 00:06:48,972
Why does she always get to pick
the kind of cookies we get? It's not fair!

33
00:06:49,075 --> 00:06:52,977
Life is not fair. Life is about the woman
getting to pick the cookies.

34
00:06:53,913 --> 00:06:56,347
Sorry, they get
a little out of control sometimes.

35
00:06:56,449 --> 00:06:58,314
They're just kids.

36
00:06:58,418 --> 00:07:01,854
But the sooner you figure out the cookie
deal, the easier your life's gonna be.

37
00:07:01,954 --> 00:07:03,353
I'm just saying.

38
00:07:03,456 --> 00:07:06,857
It's a woman's world
and we're just guests here.

39
00:07:06,959 --> 00:07:09,359
Wise man. I'd say your wife is very lucky.

40
00:07:10,930 --> 00:07:12,454
I'm not married anymore.

41
00:07:12,565 --> 00:07:17,059
I still wear it, but I lost my wife
and daughter in an accident last year.

42
00:07:17,170 --> 00:07:20,071
- Drunk driver.
- God, I'm so sorry.

43
00:07:20,173 --> 00:07:21,231
It's okay.

44
00:07:22,542 --> 00:07:25,170
- I could use a little help, though.
- Sure.

45
00:07:25,278 --> 00:07:26,575
Where is the peanut butter?

46
00:07:27,180 --> 00:07:29,978
I just moved to Portland
and I don't know this store yet.

47
00:07:31,284 --> 00:07:34,845
- It's actually two aisles over.
- This way? Thank you.

48
00:07:34,954 --> 00:07:36,319
You're so welcome.

49
00:07:37,023 --> 00:07:38,615
Remember what I told you.

50
00:07:45,932 --> 00:07:46,956
What?

51
00:08:11,757 --> 00:08:14,419
If I didn't know better,
I'd think you were following me.

52
00:08:14,660 --> 00:08:16,150
No. Hey.

53
00:08:19,699 --> 00:08:25,296
I'm not usually this forward,
but I'm recently divorced and...

54
00:08:27,807 --> 00:08:30,935
I'm taking my kids for pizza,
so I thought maybe you might want to go.

55
00:08:31,043 --> 00:08:32,032
- Pizza?
- The truth is,

56
00:08:32,144 --> 00:08:34,704
I'm just dying for some adult conversation.

57
00:08:34,814 --> 00:08:36,714
Well, I'm not usually this easy.

58
00:08:38,117 --> 00:08:39,311
David Harris.

59
00:08:40,019 --> 00:08:42,146
Susan. Susan Harding.

60
00:08:42,421 --> 00:08:45,390
- It's very nice to meet you.
- It's nice to meet you.

61
00:08:58,804 --> 00:09:00,465
I still can't believe she didn't come
to the airport.

62
00:09:00,573 --> 00:09:02,200
I told you, she had some things to do.

63
00:09:05,244 --> 00:09:07,144
- A little help here.
- Yeah.

64
00:09:10,816 --> 00:09:12,681
At least you have me.

65
00:09:16,656 --> 00:09:18,317
So, have you met this guy?

66
00:09:18,424 --> 00:09:21,518
Yeah, a couple of times. You know,
when I came by to say hi to your mom.

67
00:09:21,627 --> 00:09:23,822
- He seems cool.
- Okay, but she's only known him since,

68
00:09:23,930 --> 00:09:26,694
- what, like, after Christmas?
That's so fast. - Well...

69
00:09:27,033 --> 00:09:30,628
Come on, give it a chance. You know?
Before you do something stupid.

70
00:09:30,736 --> 00:09:33,933
- Like what?
- I don't know. Like,

71
00:09:34,040 --> 00:09:36,304
irritating your mom
and getting sent back to military school.

72
00:09:36,409 --> 00:09:40,778
I'm just saying, it seems like
she's rushing into things. Don't you think?

73
00:09:40,880 --> 00:09:43,110
I think it's her business what she does
with her personal life.

74
00:09:43,215 --> 00:09:44,978
And she tends to screw that up, mostly.

75
00:09:45,084 --> 00:09:48,781
Come on, Michael, chill on this one, please?
No fights with your mom.

76
00:09:48,888 --> 00:09:51,015
- Okay.
- Okay. I got something to show you.

77
00:09:52,792 --> 00:09:54,089
Surprise!

78
00:09:58,197 --> 00:10:01,360
Well, this is a surprise.
This is a surprise. Thank you.

79
00:10:01,734 --> 00:10:04,965
- I'm so happy to have you home.
- Hey, Michael. What's up?

80
00:10:05,071 --> 00:10:08,939
- Hey. Sean. Holy crap, you're huge.
- Thanks.

81
00:10:09,041 --> 00:10:12,533
- I missed you. Come here.
- Beth. I missed you, too.

82
00:10:12,645 --> 00:10:14,408
- Welcome home.
- Hey, Aunt Jackie.

83
00:10:14,513 --> 00:10:16,845
- Leah, hey.
- Hi, sweetie.

84
00:10:16,949 --> 00:10:19,918
Let me look at you.
Your hair's gotten longer.

85
00:10:20,019 --> 00:10:22,954
- Yeah. They ease up on you after a year.
- You look so...

86
00:10:23,055 --> 00:10:26,547
So much like a man. I was expecting a boy.

87
00:10:27,259 --> 00:10:32,219
That's what the military does. Builds men.
Good, strong men.

88
00:10:32,331 --> 00:10:34,526
Michael, this is David. David, Michael.

89
00:10:38,771 --> 00:10:41,262
- Is that a regulation cut?
- No.

90
00:10:41,374 --> 00:10:43,706
It wasn't real military.
It was just a school for screwups.

91
00:10:44,910 --> 00:10:49,176
Well, good to finally meet you.
I've heard so much about you.

92
00:10:59,725 --> 00:11:01,659
Everything seems to be going great.

93
00:11:01,761 --> 00:11:04,457
- Sean and Beth love him.
- What's not to love?

94
00:11:04,563 --> 00:11:07,999
- Yeah, he's almost too good to be true.
- Don't start, Jackie.

95
00:11:08,100 --> 00:11:10,625
I'm kidding. I'm kidding. I like him.

96
00:11:11,037 --> 00:11:14,564
Do you think I'm crazy to be engaged
to someone I've only known for six months?

97
00:11:14,674 --> 00:11:17,234
You've always been crazy.
That has nothing to do with him.

98
00:11:18,077 --> 00:11:20,841
He seems a little crazy, too, about you.

99
00:11:20,946 --> 00:11:23,346
- Everyone have enough to eat?
- Yeah...

100
00:11:23,449 --> 00:11:27,283
I would like to propose a toast.

101
00:11:28,254 --> 00:11:31,690
First of all, I want to thank
Susan and Sean and Beth,

102
00:11:31,791 --> 00:11:36,353
who, in a very short time, have taken me in
and made me feel at home.

103
00:11:36,862 --> 00:11:39,831
This is... It's a dream come true for me.

104
00:11:40,966 --> 00:11:42,263
Thank you.

105
00:11:42,401 --> 00:11:47,566
And to Michael.
Your return makes us complete.

106
00:11:48,708 --> 00:11:52,542
Family is the most important thing.
Without it, we have nothing.

107
00:11:52,878 --> 00:11:55,176
- Welcome home, Michael.
- Hear, hear.

108
00:11:55,514 --> 00:11:57,414
Hear, hear, Michael.

109
00:11:57,516 --> 00:11:59,984
I think I'm a little nauseous after that.

110
00:12:00,186 --> 00:12:01,380
Stop it.

111
00:12:02,922 --> 00:12:05,823
- You want something to drink?
- No, no, no, I got this.

112
00:12:06,325 --> 00:12:08,589
We have a surprise for you, too.

113
00:12:08,694 --> 00:12:10,753
- Really?
- Jackie pulled a few strings

114
00:12:10,863 --> 00:12:14,230
and she can get you a job
working with her as a real estate agent.

115
00:12:14,333 --> 00:12:17,393
- I couldn't.
- Wait a minute. Of course you can.

116
00:12:17,503 --> 00:12:20,233
Okay? Just follow me around
and I'll get you all set up.

117
00:12:20,339 --> 00:12:23,240
It's a great opportunity for us
and she really went out of her way.

118
00:12:23,342 --> 00:12:28,143
Well, I can't say no to my bride-to-be
or her sister, can I?

119
00:12:28,247 --> 00:12:30,181
- Thank you, Jackie.
- Don't thank me. Thank her.

120
00:12:30,282 --> 00:12:32,580
Because she's the one who convinced me
to get you off the road

121
00:12:32,685 --> 00:12:35,950
- so she can keep an eye on you.
- Did you?

122
00:12:39,959 --> 00:12:43,224
Thank you.
I'm gonna go have a word with your son.

123
00:12:44,463 --> 00:12:46,863
God, I hope Michael takes to him.

124
00:12:46,966 --> 00:12:50,925
He will.
He's just been blindsided by the divorce.

125
00:12:51,036 --> 00:12:52,503
He'll bounce back.

126
00:12:52,872 --> 00:12:56,467
Michael. Give me four minutes.
Meet me in the basement.

127
00:13:00,146 --> 00:13:03,377
So, what'd he say?

128
00:13:04,016 --> 00:13:05,711
He said he wants me
to meet him in the basement.

129
00:13:05,818 --> 00:13:07,683
- In the basement?
- Yeah.

130
00:13:08,521 --> 00:13:09,545
Why?

131
00:13:09,655 --> 00:13:11,680
I don't know.
Well, I guess I'm about to find out.

132
00:13:51,197 --> 00:13:54,724
Those two are mine.
But you're welcome to use the others.

133
00:13:56,268 --> 00:13:57,758
What's all this for?

134
00:13:57,870 --> 00:14:01,067
Well, I'm a bit of a wannabe carpenter.

135
00:14:01,173 --> 00:14:03,198
I built these storage cabinets myself.

136
00:14:03,709 --> 00:14:07,076
And I'm working up in the attic right now
on some termite damage.

137
00:14:07,913 --> 00:14:10,143
I think we need a real toast.

138
00:14:10,249 --> 00:14:11,841
Just the guys.

139
00:14:12,685 --> 00:14:15,245
This is where I keep the good stuff.

140
00:14:18,591 --> 00:14:20,115
There we go.

141
00:14:20,926 --> 00:14:24,020
Now, don't let your mom know
I've got a tequila stash.

142
00:14:24,697 --> 00:14:28,326
I've worked my ass off
trying to convince her I'm perfect.

143
00:14:28,434 --> 00:14:32,393
I know this must be a bit of a shock,
your mom and me getting married and all,

144
00:14:33,706 --> 00:14:36,539
but I want you to know, I want us

145
00:14:37,610 --> 00:14:38,975
to be a real family.

146
00:14:39,645 --> 00:14:41,510
Because without it, we have nothing?

147
00:14:43,515 --> 00:14:45,312
Okay. Touché.

148
00:14:45,885 --> 00:14:48,911
So I get a little corny sometimes,
but I meant what I said.

149
00:14:49,021 --> 00:14:51,012
You just let me handle your mother,

150
00:14:51,123 --> 00:14:54,092
and I'm gonna make sure you stay right here,
where you belong.

151
00:14:54,193 --> 00:14:56,525
No more military school.

152
00:14:56,629 --> 00:14:59,621
We're gonna put this family back together,
you and me,

153
00:14:59,732 --> 00:15:02,132
- father and son.
- Stepfather.

154
00:15:03,202 --> 00:15:04,464
Stepfather

155
00:15:05,738 --> 00:15:07,035
and son.

156
00:15:10,976 --> 00:15:12,637
That's smooth, isn't it?

157
00:15:15,481 --> 00:15:17,711
So your mother tells me
you're one hell of a swimmer.

158
00:15:17,816 --> 00:15:19,181
Yeah, I do okay.

159
00:15:19,285 --> 00:15:23,244
You know, I used to swim in competition.
In college, at U of O.

160
00:15:23,355 --> 00:15:26,017
Your senior year is gonna be very important.

161
00:15:26,125 --> 00:15:28,457
You could maybe get
a college scholarship swimming.

162
00:15:28,560 --> 00:15:29,822
You should be training this summer.

163
00:15:29,929 --> 00:15:31,556
It's kind of hard to train
in a backyard pool.

164
00:15:31,664 --> 00:15:34,462
Maybe. But I hear your old school
has a summer swim program.

165
00:15:34,566 --> 00:15:38,024
It does, but I can't use that pool anymore.

166
00:15:39,204 --> 00:15:40,637
That's the past.

167
00:15:42,741 --> 00:15:44,834
Here is to the future.

168
00:15:47,980 --> 00:15:49,811
Remember, I have to go see
my grandparents tomorrow.

169
00:15:49,915 --> 00:15:52,645
- Yeah, that's right.
- But I'll be back the day after. I'm sorry.

170
00:15:52,751 --> 00:15:56,585
No, that's all right. I mean, it's the day I get
back, but that's fine. I'll call someone else.

171
00:15:56,689 --> 00:15:58,657
Shut up. I'm sorry.

172
00:15:59,158 --> 00:16:00,989
Listen, I want to get my license.

173
00:16:01,694 --> 00:16:04,390
So, can you take me by the DMV?

174
00:16:04,763 --> 00:16:08,529
- Maybe. I'll think about it.
- Why not?

175
00:16:08,901 --> 00:16:11,369
I kind of like having you
dependent on me, actually.

176
00:16:11,470 --> 00:16:12,596
All right, get in the car.

177
00:16:12,705 --> 00:16:14,866
- Good night.
- Good night.

178
00:16:15,541 --> 00:16:17,475
- Good night, Leah.
- Bye.

179
00:16:20,512 --> 00:16:22,377
Glad you're home, Michael.

180
00:16:22,681 --> 00:16:26,777
Thanks, Aunt Jackie. I'm so glad to be home.
Thank you for coming.

181
00:16:38,897 --> 00:16:41,798
Do you think David meant what he said
about getting your mom to let you stay?

182
00:16:41,900 --> 00:16:45,165
He said he was gonna make it happen,
so we'll see.

183
00:16:45,504 --> 00:16:47,563
Sweet. Bye.

184
00:16:51,243 --> 00:16:52,938
A lot for one day, huh?

185
00:16:53,045 --> 00:16:55,912
No, no, it was... It was nice. Thanks.

186
00:16:56,281 --> 00:16:58,511
I'm trying too hard. You can say it.

187
00:17:03,856 --> 00:17:08,452
Look, Michael, I know it's difficult
to come home to another man in the house.

188
00:17:10,062 --> 00:17:12,326
I just need you to try and get along, okay?

189
00:17:12,431 --> 00:17:16,663
Mom, can we just hold the lectures, please?
I've been home for two seconds.

190
00:17:18,337 --> 00:17:19,702
Okay.

191
00:17:20,839 --> 00:17:22,466
He's a really good guy.

192
00:17:22,941 --> 00:17:25,774
And he cares about me and we're
trying to start a new life together.

193
00:17:25,878 --> 00:17:28,005
- And you don't want me to mess that up.
- Well, that's not fair.

194
00:17:28,113 --> 00:17:30,638
No, no, no, I get it. I'll try not to
inconvenience you and your new life.

195
00:17:30,749 --> 00:17:32,842
- Michael.
- I'm sorry. I...

196
00:17:33,786 --> 00:17:35,310
I'm pretty tired, Mom.

197
00:17:37,456 --> 00:17:38,980
Okay. Okay.

198
00:17:40,626 --> 00:17:42,184
Good night.

199
00:17:48,300 --> 00:17:50,325
Maybe he should stay there his senior year.

200
00:17:50,436 --> 00:17:55,135
- But his place is here with his family.
- Yeah, but you don't know what he was like.

201
00:17:55,240 --> 00:17:59,836
The kids he was hanging out with, the lying.
His temper was out of control.

202
00:18:03,882 --> 00:18:06,442
Believe me, I want him here
more than anything in the world.

203
00:18:06,552 --> 00:18:09,521
I just hope he's ready.

204
00:18:12,925 --> 00:18:14,222
You're right.

205
00:18:19,498 --> 00:18:21,557
Are you ready?

206
00:18:21,667 --> 00:18:23,362
Well, it depends.

207
00:18:24,069 --> 00:18:25,969
Are you ready for it?

208
00:19:03,041 --> 00:19:05,475
- That smells good.
- Hey.

209
00:19:05,577 --> 00:19:09,274
- How was work?
- Work was great. These are for you.

210
00:19:11,283 --> 00:19:13,114
- Thank you.
- Michael.

211
00:19:13,952 --> 00:19:15,943
- What's this?
- Your locker key to the boys' gym

212
00:19:16,054 --> 00:19:17,544
at your old high school.

213
00:19:17,656 --> 00:19:21,683
The swim team starts training
first week in July.

214
00:19:24,096 --> 00:19:25,586
Wait, how did you swing this?

215
00:19:25,697 --> 00:19:28,165
I had a little chat with Mrs. Rivers,
the athletic director,

216
00:19:28,267 --> 00:19:29,461
a very open-minded woman.

217
00:19:29,568 --> 00:19:31,058
David, that was so sweet.

218
00:19:31,170 --> 00:19:33,229
Yeah, that's incredible.

219
00:19:33,338 --> 00:19:35,829
It's just a probationary period for now.

220
00:19:35,941 --> 00:19:40,071
There's no guarantee they'll let you back
in the fall. But we'll work on that later.

221
00:19:41,780 --> 00:19:44,772
- It means a lot. Thank you so much.
- You're welcome.

222
00:19:45,717 --> 00:19:47,150
So, what are we having here?

223
00:19:47,252 --> 00:19:51,279
Okay, I just think it's so cool that he
actually did what he said he was gonna do.

224
00:19:51,390 --> 00:19:52,823
I know. I know.

225
00:19:52,925 --> 00:19:54,984
See, I told you
everything was gonna work out.

226
00:19:55,093 --> 00:19:56,822
<i>Yeah, maybe you're right.</i>

227
00:19:56,929 --> 00:20:00,990
- Hey, we still going to the DMV tomorrow?
- Yeah. I'll be by around 10:00.

228
00:20:01,433 --> 00:20:03,060
<i>- Yeah, that sounds good.
- All right.</i>

229
00:20:03,168 --> 00:20:04,294
<i>- Good night.
- Night.</i>

