Are you okay, Sean?

472
00:37:13,698 --> 00:37:14,824
Yeah.

473
00:37:16,968 --> 00:37:18,902
I guess I shouldn't have told Dad.

474
00:37:19,537 --> 00:37:21,505
- Well, what...
- No, it wasn't your fault, Sean.

475
00:37:25,176 --> 00:37:28,703
I shouldn't have done what I did.
It wasn't right.

476
00:37:31,482 --> 00:37:33,040
I'm not your father.

477
00:37:33,150 --> 00:37:35,983
Maybe someday, but...

478
00:37:37,588 --> 00:37:41,046
This is all new to me again.
I'm gonna make mistakes.

479
00:37:41,926 --> 00:37:44,827
And I just hope
you can forgive me when I do.

480
00:37:46,964 --> 00:37:48,261
Can you do that?

481
00:37:49,700 --> 00:37:51,133
I promise,

482
00:37:51,969 --> 00:37:54,301
it'll never happen again, okay?

483
00:37:56,407 --> 00:37:57,601
Friends?

484
00:38:00,878 --> 00:38:03,972
- Friends.
- Yeah. All right.

485
00:38:33,678 --> 00:38:35,202
I shouldn't have done it.

486
00:38:36,414 --> 00:38:37,847
It's just that

487
00:38:38,249 --> 00:38:43,084
I see a family without a father and I know
how easy it can all fall apart.

488
00:38:47,725 --> 00:38:50,751
If I'm ever gonna be a part of you,
I need to gain their respect.

489
00:38:50,861 --> 00:38:52,761
And trust.

490
00:38:52,863 --> 00:38:56,526
I don't know how you were raised, David,
but my family never used physical force.

491
00:38:56,634 --> 00:38:58,568
It's not okay with me.

492
00:39:00,237 --> 00:39:01,329
Sure.

493
00:39:02,073 --> 00:39:03,540
You're right.

494
00:39:35,906 --> 00:39:42,368
I can't keep... I can't... I
can't... I got to make this work...

495
00:39:53,991 --> 00:39:56,050
It's all right. It's all right.

496
00:39:56,160 --> 00:39:58,458
I'll tell her I'm sorry.
I'm sorry. I'm sorry. It's just...

497
00:40:41,405 --> 00:40:42,372
Thanks.

498
00:40:44,642 --> 00:40:47,167
- David.
- Yes. Something wrong?

499
00:40:47,478 --> 00:40:50,003
No. No, in fact, everything's great.

500
00:40:50,114 --> 00:40:53,550
Your enthusiasm with the buyers
at the Reeves' open house made the sale.

501
00:40:53,651 --> 00:40:54,811
Great.

502
00:40:55,319 --> 00:40:57,116
- We need these filled out.
- What are they?

503
00:40:57,221 --> 00:41:00,190
Social Security, payroll insurance,
workman's comp.

504
00:41:00,291 --> 00:41:04,091
And we need a picture ID. Personnel said
that they gave you the forms to fill out,

505
00:41:04,195 --> 00:41:07,221
- but they just never got them back.
- No, no, I never got anything.

506
00:41:07,331 --> 00:41:09,196
Don't worry about it. We need them, though,

507
00:41:09,300 --> 00:41:11,860
so we don't have to keep paying you
under the table.

508
00:41:11,969 --> 00:41:14,369
- I'll get all this done right away.
- Great.

509
00:41:20,945 --> 00:41:24,039
It just wasn't something
I enjoyed doing, that's all.

510
00:41:24,148 --> 00:41:28,949
Well, I don't understand,
because Jackie said you were a natural.

511
00:41:29,053 --> 00:41:30,611
Real estate is just not me.

512
00:41:30,721 --> 00:41:33,281
Well, what does that mean?
That you want to go back on the road again?

513
00:41:33,390 --> 00:41:36,518
- I don't know. We'll see. We'll see.
- No, wait. I...

514
00:41:37,495 --> 00:41:41,522
I thought you enjoyed family.
I mean, dinners like...

515
00:41:41,632 --> 00:41:45,864
I know how much you hate me being gone,
but it's what I know best.

516
00:41:49,540 --> 00:41:52,031
Let me get on your computer
and look around.

517
00:41:52,142 --> 00:41:55,873
Maybe I can find something
that doesn't require much travel.

518
00:42:04,622 --> 00:42:07,682
- Dude, you better turn it down.
- Are you worried about David?

519
00:42:07,791 --> 00:42:10,487
He's not gonna touch you, all right?
I'll make sure.

520
00:42:13,931 --> 00:42:15,455
I'm just useless.

521
00:42:15,799 --> 00:42:20,099
Hey. I'm walking out the door right now.
Okay, see you.

522
00:42:24,341 --> 00:42:25,467
How's it going?

523
00:42:26,076 --> 00:42:27,475
Couple of things down in Eugene.

524
00:42:27,578 --> 00:42:31,275
Okay, well, I'm gonna go meet Jackie
and Leah for a drink and plan the wedding.

525
00:42:31,382 --> 00:42:33,714
- Would you like to come?
- I don't think so.

526
00:42:33,817 --> 00:42:35,478
When I'm done with this,
I'm gonna go for a run.

527
00:42:35,586 --> 00:42:36,678
Okay.

528
00:42:43,861 --> 00:42:45,055
David...

529
00:42:46,463 --> 00:42:48,727
I didn't mean to make such a fuss
about your work and all.

530
00:42:48,832 --> 00:42:51,027
I don't want you to do anything
you don't want to do.

531
00:42:53,137 --> 00:42:54,195
I

532
00:42:56,574 --> 00:42:58,974
want you to be as happy as I am.

533
00:43:00,911 --> 00:43:02,208
Have fun.

534
00:43:40,484 --> 00:43:42,315
- Susan's not here.
- How about the kids?

535
00:43:42,419 --> 00:43:45,388
Beth's at a friend's. Sean and Michael
are upstairs playing video games.

536
00:43:47,124 --> 00:43:48,148
Look...

537
00:43:49,927 --> 00:43:51,827
I'm sorry about the other night.

538
00:43:51,929 --> 00:43:55,262
I made an ass out of myself.
It's just when Susan and I fight...

539
00:44:01,538 --> 00:44:05,975
I was headed to the airport.
I wanted to say goodbye to the kids and...

540
00:44:07,077 --> 00:44:10,012
Well, I'd like to apologize to you

541
00:44:10,114 --> 00:44:11,604
for being a jerk.

542
00:44:14,718 --> 00:44:17,949
Apology accepted.
Come on in and say goodbye.

543
00:44:23,594 --> 00:44:26,791
Hey, Michael tells me you used to swim
for the Ducks?

544
00:44:26,897 --> 00:44:28,023
A long time ago.

545
00:44:28,132 --> 00:44:29,827
- Yeah? What year?
- '92.

546
00:44:29,933 --> 00:44:33,164
Really? I went to U of O myself.

547
00:44:34,905 --> 00:44:38,363
- I got to grab that. Excuse me.
- Sure. Sure.

548
00:44:44,581 --> 00:44:45,809
- Hello.
- Hey.

549
00:44:45,916 --> 00:44:48,043
Jay had left a message on my cell phone

550
00:44:48,152 --> 00:44:50,916
saying he was gonna stop by there
to say goodbye to the kids.

551
00:44:51,021 --> 00:44:54,479
<i>- Did he come yet?
- No. Not yet.</i>

552
00:44:54,591 --> 00:44:57,651
<i>Okay, well, if he does,
will you just stay out of the way?</i>

553
00:44:58,962 --> 00:45:01,590
All right. I'll see you later then.

554
00:45:05,335 --> 00:45:07,667
Hey, you want to hear something funny?

555
00:45:07,771 --> 00:45:09,534
I called the alumni office

556
00:45:09,640 --> 00:45:12,905
and they told me they only had four guys
named David Harris

557
00:45:13,010 --> 00:45:15,240
graduate in the last 30 years.

558
00:45:15,879 --> 00:45:19,076
And two of them are dead
and one graduated in '87.

559
00:45:19,483 --> 00:45:22,850
And the other one was that
All-American running back.

560
00:45:22,953 --> 00:45:24,250
You remember him?

561
00:45:25,189 --> 00:45:29,091
Of course, he's a little darker
than you are, wouldn't you say?

562
00:45:30,060 --> 00:45:31,254
So...

563
00:45:32,930 --> 00:45:35,694
It's just...
It seems like you might have lied to Michael

564
00:45:35,799 --> 00:45:38,165
about college and swimming.

565
00:45:39,269 --> 00:45:42,204
And now it's got me wondering

566
00:45:42,306 --> 00:45:45,537
just, you know,
what else you might've lied about.

567
00:45:58,489 --> 00:46:01,253
Hey, look, I told Michael
that I would do some checking on you

568
00:46:01,358 --> 00:46:03,883
and, to be honest, I'd like some answers.

569
00:46:06,897 --> 00:46:09,092
Hey. You hear me?

570
00:46:10,234 --> 00:46:11,326
Yep.

571
00:46:19,443 --> 00:46:22,071
- What?
- I heard something.

572
00:46:34,858 --> 00:46:36,655
What was it?

573
00:46:36,760 --> 00:46:38,955
I don't know. It's nothing.

574
00:46:44,034 --> 00:46:46,002
I don't understand.
I'm kind of confused, because...

575
00:46:46,103 --> 00:46:47,365
About?

576
00:46:47,471 --> 00:46:49,598
Well, the feedback
from the buyers was great.

577
00:46:49,706 --> 00:46:53,472
He just felt that it wasn't
what he thought it was gonna be.

578
00:46:53,577 --> 00:46:54,669
You're okay with him on the road?

579
00:46:54,778 --> 00:46:58,179
He's gonna try to find something
where he doesn't have to travel that much.

580
00:46:58,816 --> 00:47:03,048
And I just want him to be happy.
If he's happy, I'm happy.

581
00:47:03,587 --> 00:47:06,249
There you go. I just want to get his bags.

582
00:47:09,026 --> 00:47:11,324
- Pop the trunk?
- You got it.

583
00:47:49,299 --> 00:47:51,597
<i>This is Jay Harding. Leave a message.</i>

584
00:47:51,702 --> 00:47:53,567
Hey, Dad. It's me.

585
00:47:55,572 --> 00:47:58,632
Where are you? Call me. Bye.

586
00:48:20,931 --> 00:48:22,159
David!

587
00:48:23,934 --> 00:48:25,196
Yeah, what do you need, Michael?

588
00:48:33,243 --> 00:48:34,471
Nothing.

589
00:48:42,586 --> 00:48:45,646
You know when you asked me
at Michael's party

590
00:48:45,756 --> 00:48:47,883
if I thought you were rushing into things?

591
00:48:49,426 --> 00:48:51,155
I'm thinking now that maybe you are.

592
00:48:51,762 --> 00:48:54,424
I mean, how much
do you really know about David?

593
00:48:54,531 --> 00:49:00,197
The same day that I ask him for details
about his past, he just up and quits.

594
00:49:00,304 --> 00:49:03,364
- You don't find that strange?
- No, I don't.

595
00:49:06,143 --> 00:49:09,670
You know what I want to do?
I want to go to Vegas

596
00:49:09,780 --> 00:49:13,079
- and have one of those 10-minute weddings.
- Nice.

597
00:49:14,051 --> 00:49:16,349
David wants to have a church wedding.

598
00:49:16,453 --> 00:49:19,911
That's great. What church? I mean,
do you even know what religion he is?

599
00:49:20,457 --> 00:49:22,322
I don't care what goddamn religion he is.

600
00:49:25,662 --> 00:49:29,689
Okay, you're starting
to sound just like Jay.

601
00:49:29,800 --> 00:49:33,361
He's accused me of not knowing anything
about David. You know what I do know?

602
00:49:33,470 --> 00:49:35,233
David has been good to me.

603
00:49:35,339 --> 00:49:38,035
He's good to the kids. They love him.

604
00:49:38,675 --> 00:49:41,906
He's made my life worth living again.
I mean, I...

605
00:49:42,946 --> 00:49:44,607
For the first time in a long time,

606
00:49:44,715 --> 00:49:47,183
I'm looking forward
to the future with a smile.

607
00:49:47,284 --> 00:49:53,280
I just wish everybody would be
happy for me. Is that too much to ask?

608
00:49:54,858 --> 00:49:56,189
No, it's not.

609
00:49:56,293 --> 00:49:59,820
Personally, I'm with you. Hey, I'd have
my teeth cleaned in Vegas if I could.

610
00:50:00,564 --> 00:50:01,861
Right?

611
00:50:02,499 --> 00:50:06,458
- Go! Go! Go! Watch it! Wow!
- I just missed that car.

612
00:50:06,570 --> 00:50:07,969
- Hey, guys.
- Hey.

613
00:50:08,071 --> 00:50:09,834
- Hey, Mom.
- How'd it go with Jackie and Leah?

614
00:50:09,940 --> 00:50:13,103
We decided we should go to Vegas.

615
00:50:14,378 --> 00:50:16,972
- I'll be right back.
- Where's Michael?

616
00:50:18,048 --> 00:50:19,538
He's in his room.

617
00:50:19,649 --> 00:50:22,618
I think he's a little upset
that his father never showed.

618
00:50:24,454 --> 00:50:26,422
That is so typical of Jay.

619
00:50:29,092 --> 00:50:30,582
- Honey?
- Yeah.

620
00:50:30,994 --> 00:50:33,326
I have a confession to make.

621
00:50:35,232 --> 00:50:39,566
I accidentally broke the crystal vase
that was in the living room.

622
00:50:46,410 --> 00:50:47,843
That's okay.

623
00:50:47,944 --> 00:50:51,107
It was a wedding gift from Jay's sister.
I never liked it anyway.

624
00:50:51,214 --> 00:50:52,875
You didn't?

625
00:50:52,983 --> 00:50:55,611
- Or her.
- Then I don't feel so bad.

626
00:51:02,159 --> 00:51:04,184
You don't think it's a little weird

627
00:51:04,294 --> 00:51:07,320
that I ask for some background information,
and suddenly,

628
00:51:07,431 --> 00:51:09,296
he doesn't want to sell real estate anymore?

629
00:51:09,399 --> 00:51:11,333
Not necessarily.

630
00:51:11,435 --> 00:51:13,835
I like David. He's a gentleman.

631
00:51:13,937 --> 00:51:16,497
He always picks up the tab.
Jay was so cheap.

632
00:51:16,606 --> 00:51:20,667
Do you know what I do think is weird,
though? He always pays in cash.

633
00:51:20,777 --> 00:51:22,870
Who doesn't want the miles?

634
00:51:30,020 --> 00:51:33,478
You know, I never thought
I would ever say this,

635
00:51:35,058 --> 00:51:37,618
but I think I'm gonna give Jay a call.

636
00:51:37,727 --> 00:51:42,755
I mean, if he's not buying this either,
then maybe it's worth checking into.

637
00:51:48,705 --> 00:51:51,196
Hey. He didn't show up?

638
00:51:52,809 --> 00:51:53,935
No.

639
00:51:55,846 --> 00:51:57,313
I'm so sorry.

640
00:51:57,414 --> 00:51:59,848
- That's okay.
- No, it's not okay.

641
00:51:59,950 --> 00:52:02,510
He's never been there for you
like a father should be.

642
00:52:02,619 --> 00:52:03,745
And part of that's my fault

643
00:52:03,854 --> 00:52:06,448
because I never should have allowed it
to go on as long as it did.

644
00:52:07,858 --> 00:52:11,851
That's why David's so important to me.
Because he cares about you kids.

645
00:52:11,962 --> 00:52:14,658
He wants you to be here
and be part of your lives.

646
00:52:14,764 --> 00:52:16,755
He's so perfect, isn't he?

647
00:52:19,402 --> 00:52:20,994
Take those off.

648
00:52:23,340 --> 00:52:26,605
I thought you'd be able to see
how happy David makes me.

649
00:52:26,710 --> 00:52:28,371
He is part of this family now.

650
00:52:28,478 --> 00:52:31,936
I want him in my life and our lives
and you need to understand that.

651
00:52:32,048 --> 00:52:35,245
- Do you understand that, Michael?
- Yeah. I understand. Okay?

652
00:52:41,791 --> 00:52:42,917
Okay.

